  "couName": "CPB use",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally during model development to evaluate the influence of viscosity and rotational speed on the relative hemolysis index; results confirmed low parametric sensitivity across the five operating points and were documented in the engineering notebook. No formal UQ propagation was deemed necessary at MRL 2, and the screening results are referenced narratively here rather than as a structured sensitivity analysis node.",
