    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/org/computational-biofluid-lab",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels at MRL 2. Grid convergence index confirmed below threshold. Validation against FDA pump benchmark demonstrates adequate predictive capability for relative hemolysis index. A screening sensitivity study performed during model development confirmed low parametric sensitivity of RH to viscosity and rotational speed perturbations across all five operating points, providing additional confidence in model robustness. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per the ASME V&V 40 factor requirements table. The credibility evidence package is sufficient to support the regulatory decision that the CFD model adequately predicts worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for this Class II CPB device.",
